  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e01\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453323008/h2BEA29C3/resume-proficiel-pre\" id=\"_r_a_10453323008\" width=\"800\" height=\"420\" alt=\"Resume Proficiel Pre\" title=\"\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003csub\u003eThe image does not depict the actual subjects of the story. Subjects are models.\u003c/sub\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e02\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453310720/hE6BD2BA4/whatever-resume-template-they-are-using-combining-jobs-because-want-list-4-but-template-has-space-3\" id=\"_r_a_10453310720\" width=\"730\" height=\"938\" alt=\"curiouspursuit People who tie themselves in knots to fit exactly into whatever resume template they are using. Combining jobs because you want to list 4 but the template has space for 3.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e03\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453311744/h912A95A6/section-and-ask-are-trying-tell-person-reading-this-and-if-cant-answe-question-doesnt-need-be-there\" id=\"_r_a_10453311744\" width=\"576\" height=\"962\" alt=\"Using a template with like 8 bullet points for \u0026#34;awards\u0026#34; and digging so deep you\u0026#39;re listing \u0026#34;second grader of the month May 1992\u0026#34; I usually point to the offending section and ask \u0026#34;what are you trying to tell the person reading this?\u0026#34; And if you cant answe that question it doesn\u0026#39;t need to be there.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOk, this is fair, but what if the thing you \u003ci\u003eare \u003c/i\u003etrying to communicate is that you were named Best Second Grader of the month? All jokes aside, it\u0026#39;s true that so many folks cram way too much information into their resume rather than thinking of their CV as a pitch—a narrative you are trying to create about yourself and your journey.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e04\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453311488/hED019707/name-contact-info-high-school-info-and-1-job-experience-mcdonalds-whole-resume-13rd-sheet-paper\" id=\"_r_a_10453311488\" width=\"586\" height=\"544\" alt=\"[deleted] Typos, irrelevant information especially, recently a resume came in that had the person\u0026#39;s name, contact info, high school info, and 1 job experience: McDonalds. The whole resume was 1/3rd sheet of paper.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e05\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453310976/h60EC8D5F/long-walks-on-beach-really-dont-have-time-read-even-page-submit-so-if-has-be-page-better-be-good\" id=\"_r_a_10453310976\" width=\"596\" height=\"430\" alt=\"We loved it, its all we needed to know, compared to mr. I like to take long walks on the beach. We really don\u0026#39;t have time to read even the page you submit, so if it has to be a page, it better be good.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e06\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453312512/h6C8D60FB/higher-position-still-5-pages-kicker-is-one-pages-full-blown-headshot-selfie-he-didnt-get-call-back\" id=\"_r_a_10453312512\" width=\"586\" height=\"522\" alt=\"Also we had a guy send a 5 page resume, which is extreme but it was for a higher position, still 5 pages. The kicker is that one of the pages was a full blown headshot selfie. He didn\u0026#39;t get a call back\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBrevity is the soul of wit, as they say! Sometimes, you don\u0026#39;t need to reveal everything you\u0026#39;ve ever done to prove that you\u0026#39;re qualified for one job.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e07\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453310464/h5E4D907C/had-resume-once-state-work-experience-being-hacker-internet-other-gems-included-resume-were\" id=\"_r_a_10453310464\" width=\"596\" height=\"406\" alt=\"neibegafig I had a resume once state for work experience being \u0026#34;Hacker - The Internet\u0026#34; Other gems included in the resume were:\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e08\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453311232/h6D97F608/things-never-been-convicted-computer-crime-will-admit-gave-chuckle-but-certainly-deterrant-job\" id=\"_r_a_10453311232\" width=\"592\" height=\"524\" alt=\"\u0026#34;I\u0026#39;ve been both fired and hired for hacking various things\u0026#34; \u0026#34;I\u0026#39;ve never been. convicted of a computer crime\u0026#34; I will admit it gave me a chuckle but certainly was a deterrant for the job.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e09\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453312000/h1735BE35/deleted-they-have-just-stacks-and-stacks-pages-like-40-page-resumes\" id=\"_r_a_10453312000\" width=\"602\" height=\"298\" alt=\"[deleted]. They have just stacks and stacks of pages. Like 40 page resumes.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e40 pages?! Were they in the CIA?!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e10\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453312256/h375978BD/as-simple-as-capital-letters-at-start-sentences-and-capitalizing-words-do-not-need-be-capitalized\" id=\"_r_a_10453312256\" width=\"568\" height=\"414\" alt=\"Zhaelthas not using something as simple as capital letters at the start of sentences. and capitalizing Words that do not need to be capitalized.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhat if that\u0026#39;s their ~writerly voice~ though? Just kidding! Proofread your work before rage-applying to jobs, people!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e11\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453312768/h2E0B10C5/an-email-with-small-pointers-and-improvements-he-could-do-on-his-resume-doing-my-civic-duty-yippee\" id=\"_r_a_10453312768\" width=\"602\" height=\"750\" alt=\"Tim Not common but a couple months ago, this kid applied to my clinic for assistant stuff. The thing was in Comic Sans. Yuck. I actually felt bad so I sent him an email with small pointers and improvements he could do on his resume. Doing my civic duty yippee!\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e12\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453313280/hE9A22465/has-no-one-mentioned-bible-verse-quotes-or-do-just-get-all-nutjobs-who-think-s-appropriate-resume\" id=\"_r_a_10453313280\" width=\"574\" height=\"392\" alt=\"CreampuffOfLove How has no one mentioned the Bible verse quotes?! Or do I just get all the nutjobs who think that\u0026#39;s appropriate for a resume?\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e13\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453313024/h3EFD64E7/long-distances-without-getting-tired-edit-feel-should-add-he-applying-at-millwork-finishing-shop\" id=\"_r_a_10453313024\" width=\"582\" height=\"750\" alt=\"sixesand7s. 2 My friend had someone come into his work with a resume a few years back, one of the \u0026#34;achievements\u0026#34; he had listed was, \u0026#34;Able to walk extremely long distances without getting tired\u0026#34; EDIT: I feel I should add, he was applying at a millwork finishing shop\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe long-distance thing is impressive and could never be me! I\u0026#39;d hire that person…\u003c/p\u003e\n\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e14\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453323264/hC60DD881/resume\" id=\"_r_a_10453323264\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" alt=\"RESUME\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003csub\u003eThe image does not depict the actual subjects of the story. Subjects are models.\u003c/sub\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e15\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453313536/h28BDC0C7/while-applying-an-office-job-is-great-way-see-going-leave-as-soon-as-get-job-actually-wanted\" id=\"_r_a_10453313536\" width=\"576\" height=\"692\" alt=\"Vergils_Lost Former recruiter. The only thing I don\u0026#39;t already see mentioned here already is a mission statement for a totally different industry. \u0026#34;Looking for an exciting career in zookeeping\u0026#34; while applying to an office job is a great way to see that you\u0026#39;re going to leave as soon as you get the job you ACTUALLY wanted.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e16\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453314816/hCA027FC3/trying-create-generic-resume-just-leave-bit-out-if-know-type-career-looking-s-maybe-worth-including\" id=\"_r_a_10453314816\" width=\"604\" height=\"610\" alt=\"To a lesser extent, also really vague mission statements. That shows you have no idea what you want, which can be fine in some contexts, but is going to lose out to someone who knows they want the job in question. If you\u0026#39;re trying to create a generic resume, just leave that bit out. If you know what type of career you\u0026#39;re looking for, it\u0026#39;s maybe worth including.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e17\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453314560/hF3D73583/my-knowledge-and-grow-my-career-am-looking-learn-new-skills-and-be-challenged-and-enjoy-work-do\" id=\"_r_a_10453314560\" width=\"590\" height=\"586\" alt=\"[deleted] ⚫ A cover letter or objective that is all about what the job can do for you: \u0026#34;I am a recent graduate seeking a role where I can apply my knowledge and grow my career. I am looking to learn new skills and be challenged and to enjoy the work I do.\u0026#34;\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e18\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453314304/hB42BAACB/so-pleased-hear-want-can-offer-ask-not-employer-can-do-ask-can-do-employer\" id=\"_r_a_10453314304\" width=\"598\" height=\"316\" alt=\"I\u0026#39;m so pleased to hear what you want. What can you offer me? Ask not what your employer can do for you, ask what you can do for your employer.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo play devil\u0026#39;s advocate for a moment, this does feel like a backward mentality. Employment is, in fact, a two-way street, and both parties should present what they can offer to each other prior to an interview. Just our two cents!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e19\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453313792/h6173A011/jobs-mix-up-and-show-other-things-did-at-jobs-theyre-not-dealbreakers-course-just-annoyances\" id=\"_r_a_10453313792\" width=\"608\" height=\"714\" alt=\"Skinny Testaverde. I\u0026#39;m not a recruiter but I have been in charge of hiring, and I hate objectives. They\u0026#39;re useless and waste space, in my opinion. Also I don\u0026#39;t like repetitive bullet points; if you did the same thing at a bunch of different jobs, mix it up and show me what OTHER things you did at the jobs. They\u0026#39;re not dealbreakers of course, just annoyances.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e20\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453314048/h738DF2FD/other-day-had-someone-list-pre-school-along-with-name-school-under-their-education-section\" id=\"_r_a_10453314048\" width=\"566\" height=\"546\" alt=\"DeepFriedPlumbus. The other day I had someone list \u0026#34;Pre- School\u0026#34; along with the name of the school under their education section\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e21\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453315584/hA4A32A05/consider-have-p