s are super obvious.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e26\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453316096/hDF56FEEA/typos-any-part-resume-if-didnt-take-time-carefully-proofread-wont-take-time-do-job-well\" id=\"_r_a_10453316096\" width=\"598\" height=\"480\" alt=\"SaltYourPopcorn Typos in any part of the resume. If you didn\u0026#39;t take time to carefully proofread, you won\u0026#39;t take the time to do the job well.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e27\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453315328/h83BC2C66/tracyannk28-adding-facebook-twitter-and-instagram-under-technical-skills\" id=\"_r_a_10453315328\" width=\"518\" height=\"290\" alt=\"Tracyannk28 Adding Facebook, Twitter and Instagram under \u0026#34;technical skills\u0026#34;.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e28\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453317120/hC7F97332/deserve-at-my-best-who-puts-on-resume-does-have-do-with-camping-world-she-29-years-old-gods-sake\" id=\"_r_a_10453317120\" width=\"594\" height=\"908\" alt=\"[deleted] My brother works at camping world and told me someone wrote on their resume \u0026#34;If you don\u0026#39;t want me at my worst, you don\u0026#39;t deserve me at my best\u0026#34;. Who the puts that on a resume? What does that have to do with camping world? She was 29 years old for gods sake.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e29\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453316864/h4315ED20/outside-box-and-take-deep-dive-into-core-competencies-create-buy-and-game-changing-results-next\" id=\"_r_a_10453316864\" width=\"606\" height=\"960\" alt=\"Shoofro Ridiculous corporate jargon \u0026#34;In my last position, I leveraged synergies between business units to create value and a win-win scenario which empowered other business units to think outside the box and take a deep dive into core competencies to create buy-in and game changing results.\u0026#34; Next.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e30\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453316608/hB73CDD84/with-picture-his-face-and-pie-chart-breaking-down-his-amazing-traits-like-listening-and-dedication\" id=\"_r_a_10453316608\" width=\"572\" height=\"660\" alt=\"mazimaxi This isnt common nor should be, but im gonna share it anyway. A guy turned in a resume for a sales job with a picture of his face and a pie chart breaking down his \u0026#34;amazing\u0026#34; traits like listening and dedication.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e31\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453318144/h9FE20196/needed-s-something-recruiter-will-ask-an-person-interview-see-will-fit-within-company-environment\" id=\"_r_a_10453318144\" width=\"566\" height=\"700\" alt=\"50Shades Of Vader. I have seen a few people mention their hobbies and interests on their resume, it\u0026#39;s actually not needed. That\u0026#39;s something the recruiter will ask in an in-person interview to see how you will fit within the company environment.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e32\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453317632/hE112034D/like-they-had-never-seen-resume-before-had-students-not-even-have-their-name-on-their-own-resume\" id=\"_r_a_10453317632\" width=\"596\" height=\"1000\" alt=\"xDommy. I worked in a college career development office for a few years and what may not be the biggest mistake, but the most common was improper formatting, almost half of students that came to us for help seemed like they had never seen a resume before. We had students not even have their name on their own resume.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e33\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453317376/h370C694A/at-and-they-are-looking-might-be-perfect-someone-while-someone-else-might-hate-just-never-know\" id=\"_r_a_10453317376\" width=\"570\" height=\"876\" alt=\"enolic2000. As a recruiter/hiring manager, I can say that there is no right or wrong way to do a resume. It all depends upon who is looking at it and what they are looking for. it might be perfect for someone, while someone else might hate it. You just never know.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e34\u003c/span\u003e\n                            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10453317888/h34DD1F24/do-think-is-right-and-dont-sweat-could-be-perfect-candidate-but-they-picked-someones-kid-instead\" id=\"_r_a_10453317888\" width=\"596\" height=\"440\" alt=\"Do what you think is right and don\u0026#39;t sweat it. You could be the perfect candidate, but they picked someones kid instead.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n            \u003cp\u003eStay up to date by following us on \u003ca href=\"https://www.facebook.com/FailBlog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eFacebook\u003c/a\u003e!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                \u003ch2\u003eTags\u003c/h2\u003e\n        \n\n            \n\n            \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \n        \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eScroll down for the next article\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n                \n\n   